{
  "texts": [
    "We also find that fine-tuning LLaMA-3-8B-Instruct models on CosmosQA and MedQA generally increases CoT Pred Match values in Figure 3, indicating a decline in CoT reasoning faithfulness.",
    "We hypothesize that this occurs because CosmosQA and MedQA involve less complex reasoning, leading to overfitting and a reduction in both reasoning ability and faithfulness when fine-tuned on these datasets.",
    "Similar trends are observed in the Filler Substitution and Paraphrasing faithfulness tests.",
    "Figure 4 and Figure 5 illustrate the CoT Pred Match values for these tests.",
    "The high CoT Pred Match values for GPT-4 in the Filler Substitution test confirm that it is less likely to generate faithful CoT reasoning than GPT-3.5-turbo-0125 and LLaMA-3-8B-Instruct."
  ]
}